{"title":"Steve Potts partners with Nitto, Panaracer, Tange-Seiki & Suzue on new component line","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/08/23/steve-potts-partners-with-nitto-panaracer-tange-seiki-suzue-on-new-component-line/","date":1629732198000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><p>The legendary <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2020/03/24/long-road-to-nahbs-2020-teaser-interview-w-steve-of-steve-potts-bicycles/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Steve Potts</a> is at it again. Putting more than 40 years of experience in designing and manufacturing custom bicycle components, Potts is partnering with some friends to create a new series of parts. Probably best known for his custom titanium creations, these components will be a line of production parts that feature Potts’ engineering and design, but available off the shelf.</p><h2>Steve Potts Type II-R Forks</h2><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/23105946/Steve-Potts-Component-line-tange-seiki-suzue-1-e1629731024100.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/23105946/Steve-Potts-Component-line-tange-seiki-suzue-1-e1629731024100.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:484x542/rscb28/ng:webp/ngcb28\" alt=\"Steve Potts Type 2 R forks\" width=\"1200\" height=\"1344\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/23105946/Steve-Potts-Component-line-tange-seiki-suzue-1-e1629731024100.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/23105946/Steve-Potts-Component-line-tange-seiki-suzue-1-e1629731024100-268x300.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 268w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/23105946/Steve-Potts-Component-line-tange-seiki-suzue-1-e1629731024100-800x896.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/23105946/Steve-Potts-Component-line-tange-seiki-suzue-1-e1629731024100-107x120.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 107w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/23105946/Steve-Potts-Component-line-tange-seiki-suzue-1-e1629731024100-768x860.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/23105946/Steve-Potts-Component-line-tange-seiki-suzue-1-e1629731024100-696x780.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/23105946/Steve-Potts-Component-line-tange-seiki-suzue-1-e1629731024100-1068x1196.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/23105946/Steve-Potts-Component-line-tange-seiki-suzue-1-e1629731024100-375x420.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 375w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/23105946/Steve-Potts-Component-line-tange-seiki-suzue-1-e1629731024100.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:484x542/rscb28/ng:webp/ngcb28\" ezoid=\"0.8470875598526111\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/23105946/Steve-Potts-Component-line-tange-seiki-suzue-1-e1629731024100.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/23105946/Steve-Potts-Component-line-tange-seiki-suzue-1-e1629731024100-268x300.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 268w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/23105946/Steve-Potts-Component-line-tange-seiki-suzue-1-e1629731024100-800x896.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/23105946/Steve-Potts-Component-line-tange-seiki-suzue-1-e1629731024100-107x120.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 107w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/23105946/Steve-Potts-Component-line-tange-seiki-suzue-1-e1629731024100-768x860.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/23105946/Steve-Potts-Component-line-tange-seiki-suzue-1-e1629731024100-696x780.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/23105946/Steve-Potts-Component-line-tange-seiki-suzue-1-e1629731024100-1068x1196.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/23105946/Steve-Potts-Component-line-tange-seiki-suzue-1-e1629731024100-375x420.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 375w\"></a></p><p>Starting with the Type II-R rigid forks, this is a product that was born out of consumer demand. “I really thought demand for my rigid fork would have disappeared when suspension came on the scene, but customers kept on asking for it.” The result is this new fork which is based on the Charlie Cunningham design and will be made by Tange.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/23110018/Steve-Potts-Component-line-tange-seiki-suzue-3-scaled.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/23110018/Steve-Potts-Component-line-tange-seiki-suzue-3-488x1200.jpg\" alt=\"Steve potts rigid fork\" width=\"488\" height=\"1200\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/23110018/Steve-Potts-Component-line-tange-seiki-suzue-3-488x1200.jpg 488w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s